1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. Nf3 b4 5. a3 g6 6. axb4 cxb4 7. g3 (7. Nbd2 Bg7
8. e4 d6 $132 9. Qa4+ Nfd7 10. Qxb4 a5 11. Qa3 Na6 $44 {The a5-pawn is immune
and Black has excellent outposts for his knights, which guarantee him of rich
counterplay on the queenside. White's plans with the quick advance of the e-pawn
are given in Cha[ter 4.}) 7... Bg7 8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O a5 {[%cal Gb8a6]} 10. Nbd2
Bb7 $6 ({An idle move instead of the logical} 10... d6 $1 11. e4 Nbd7 {,
aiming at the key c5-square.}) 11. Qa4 ({White went for the advanced pawns
instead of seizing the proper moment for} 11. e4 $1 d6 12. e5 $1 dxe5 13. Nxe5
Qc7 (13... Nxd5 14. Nxf7) 14. Re1) 11... Qc7 (11... Qc8 $142) 12. Nd4 d6 13.
Nb5 Qc8 14. Nb3 Qxc4 $6 (14... Nbd7 15. Nxa5 Nb6 16. Qxb4 Nxc4 17. e4 Rxa5 18.
Rxa5 Nxa5 19. Qxa5 Ba6 20. Re1 Qb7 $44) 15. Nxa5 Qxe2 ({To sacrifice an
exchange by} 15... Rxa5 {is arguably better than the game continuation. White
stays on the top by means of} 16. Qxa5 Bxd5 17. Bxd5 Nxd5 18. Na7 $1 $16 {
[%cal Ga5b5]}) 16. Nc7 Nbd7 17. Nxa8 Rxa8 18. Qxb4 $6 (18. Bg5 $1 $16) 18...
Bxd5 19. Bxd5 (19. Re1 $5 Qh5 20. Qb5 e6) 19... Nxd5 20. Qb7 N7b6 21. Ra3 Rc8
22. Nc6 Bf8 (22... Bf6 $5) 23. Na7 (23. Nd4 Qc4 $44) 23... Rc7 (23... Rc2 $5)
24. Qb8 {[%cal Gc1h6]} Nd7 (24... Qh5 $5) 25. Qd8 (25. Qb5 $142 Qe4 26. Qa4 $14
) 25... Qh5 $2 (25... Rxc1 $5 {leads to an unusual situation after} 26. Rxc1
Qxb2 27. Rca1 (27. Raa1 Nc3 $1 {[%cal Gc3e2,Gb2b7]}) 27... Ne5 $44 {In spite
of being two exchanges (true, with a pawn for each of them) down, Black seems
to have enough counterplay.}) (25... Kg7 $5) 26. Nb5 Rb7 27. Qc8 Rxb5 28. Qxd7
Rb8 29. Ra5 $6 (29. Qa7 $16) 29... Nf6 30. Rxh5 Nxd7 31. Ra5 Nc5 32. Ra3 f5 33.
Rd1 Kf7 $44 34. Kf1 Bg7 35. Ra2 Bf6 36. h4 Rb4 {Black has achieved a lot and
is objectively out of danger. A draw is the most likely outcome, but his
opponent lost gradually the thread of the game and the opportunity to get a
positive result.} 37. Ra7 Ne4 38. Ra2 Bd4 39. b3 $6 (39. Bd2 $1 Rxb2 40. Rxb2
Bxb2 41. Be1 $11) 39... Nc3 40. Bd2 Rxb3 41. Bxc3 Bxc3 42. Ra7 Rb6 43. Rd5 Bf6
44. h5 $6 (44. f4) 44... Ke6 45. Rd3 Rb1+ 46. Ke2 gxh5 47. Ra5 Be5 (47... h4 $1
48. gxh4 Rb4 $15) 48. f4 Ba1 49. Re3+ (49. Kf3 $142) 49... Kf6 50. Ra7 $2 (50.
Ra4 $142 Rh1 51. Kf2) 50... Bd4 $1 51. Rexe7 Rb2+ 52. Kf1 Rf2+ 53. Ke1 Bxa7 54.
Rxa7 Rg2 55. Rxh7 Rxg3 56. Kf2 Rg4 57. Rh6+ Ke7 58. Kf3 h4 $19 59. Ke3 d5 60.
Rh5 Kf6 61. Rh6+ Kg7 62. Rh5 Kg6 63. Rh8 Rg3+ 64. Kf2 d4 65. Rd8 d3 66. Rd5 Kh5
67. Rxf5+ Kg4 68. Rd5 Rf3+ 0-1

