{[#]} 12... Rb8 $5 {A subtle idea to force the opponent to take on c4 with a
piece and place Bc8 on the a6-square. The other directions for it are arguably
better:} (12... Bb7 13. Qf3 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Gf6d7]} Nfd7 14. Nce4 {is a
clever try to hinder 14....Bf6 and to keep slightly better chances after the
expected disappearance of the d-pawns.}) ({or} 12... Bf5 13. Re1 $14) 13. Re1
Nxc4 14. Nxc4 Ba6 15. Ne3 {[%cal Gd1f3,Gh2h3]} Re8 16. h3 ({To} 16. Qf3 {
Black, anticipating the jump to the f5-square, will continue in the same
manner.}) 16... Bf8 17. Qf3 h6 $11 {[%csl Rf8][%cal Ga6d3]} *

