{[#]} 12... d6 $5 $146 13. Qxg7 Bf6 14. Qg3 (14. Qh6 Rg8 $1 15. g3 Rg6 16. Qd2
(16. Qxh7 $2 Qxb6 $19) 16... Bd4 17. Bg2 h5 $132) 14... Qxb6 {And here this
option is the better one, based on the idea to meet} 15. Be2 {with} Qb4+ 16.
Bd2 Qxe4 $1 {The key position - the roles of the queens have changed - now
Black is trying to keep the enemy king in the centre. Piece activity is once
again much more important than thinking about restoring the material balance.}
*

